S307 Code review and bugfix pass for Story 4B.4 Turn Timeout & AFK Escalation addressing disconnect handling edge cases (Apr 5 at 2:17 PM)
**Investigated**: Adversarial code review identified seven issues (H1, H2, M1, M2, M3, L1, L3) in the AFK escalation system's interaction with player disconnection, focusing on race conditions where the turn timer could fire for offline players, reconnection exploits that reset timers inappropriately, and defensive guards missing in vote casting paths.

**Learned**: AFK escalation must be strictly separated from disconnect handling: turn timers should cancel immediately when the current player disconnects (H1), timer expiry handlers need connection re-checks for defense-in-depth (H2), and reconnections by non-current players must not reset the stuck player's timer to prevent collusion exploits (M1). Grace-expiry owns all offline player auto-discard paths without incrementing AFK counters, while the turn timer system targets only present-but-inattentive players.

**Completed**: Applied all HIGH and MEDIUM severity fixes: turn timer cancellation on current-player disconnect (join-handler.ts), connected guard in handleTurnTimerExpiry (turn-timer.ts), conditional syncTurnTimer gating in attachToExistingSeat to resume-from-pause or current-player-only (join-handler.ts), defensive connected check in handleAfkVoteCastMessage (turn-timer.ts), and startAfkVote rejection of disconnected targets (turn-timer.ts). Added two AC9 regression tests validating extended-expiry no-op on disconnect and AFK vote prevention for offline targets. Updated T20 test name for clarity and documented defensive cleanup in handlePauseTimeout. All 300 server tests pass, typecheck clean, lint 0 errors. Story status updated from review to done in both implementation artifact and sprint-status.yaml.

**Next Steps**: Story 4B.4 complete. Session wrapped up with documentation updates and sprint tracking. Epic 4B (Multiplayer Resilience) continues with 4B.5 (dead-seat turn skip) remaining in backlog.


